Using `registerDestructor` from `@ember/destroyable` is the modern Glimmer-compatible way to run cleanup when a component is torn down. Calling `cancelAll()` inside the destructor ensures the polling loop stops immediately when the user navigates away, preventing memory leaks and ghost network requests.

