Omit `try/catch` when you only need the error to appear in `task.last.error` — ember-concurrency sets this automatically on any unhandled throw. Add `try/catch` only when you need to: distinguish `TaskCancelation` from real errors, perform side-effects on error (e.g. show a toast), or implement retry logic. Always re-throw after side-effects if you still want `last.error` to be set.

```gjs
import Component from '@glimmer/component'
import { task } from 'ember-concurrency'

// ✅ EAGER — perform on mount when data is always needed
export default class MatchDetailComponent extends Component {
  loadMatch = task({ drop: true }, async (matchId) => {
    const res = await fetch(`/api/matches/${matchId}`)
    return await res.json()
  })

