`maxConcurrency: 1` alone is NOT equivalent to `enqueue`. Without `enqueue`, `maxConcurrency: 1` uses `drop` behaviour — excess performs are discarded. `enqueue + maxConcurrency: 1` serializes all performs in order with no drops — equivalent to a single-threaded queue. The default task (no modifier) runs all instances concurrently with no limit. Always pair `maxConcurrency` with `enqueue` if you want queuing, not dropping.

