An `enqueue` task is purpose-built for exactly this pattern — each `perform()` call is queued and runs only after the previous one completes. With a `@tracked` array and `setTimeout`, you must manually track timers, handle component destruction cleanup, and deal with race conditions when notifications arrive faster than they expire. The enqueue task eliminates all of that: it queues automatically, cancels cleanly on service destruction, and the code reads as a simple sequential async routine. Always prefer enqueue tasks for ordered, time-separated work.

